Section 1:
1 L.D. 1435
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 INLAND FISHERIES AND WILDLIFE
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 944, L.D. 1435, “An Act to Allow a
10 Municipality or Locally Recognized Lake Association to Post Certain Information on the
11 Department of Inland Fisheries and Wildlife's Information Kiosks Located at State Boat
12 Launch Facilities”
13 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
14 'An Act to Allow a Municipality or Local Lake Association to Post Certain
15 Information on Informational Signs Located at State Boat Launch Facilities with
16 Department of Inland Fisheries and Wildlife Permission'
17 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
18 following:
19 'Sec. 1. 12 MRSA §12708, as amended by PL 2021, c. 184, §§10 to 12, is further
20 amended by amending the section headnote to read:
21 §12708. Wildlife management areas and public access sites; boat launch
22 informational signs
23 Sec. 2. 12 MRSA §12708, sub-§3 is enacted to read:
24 3. Boat launch informational signs. Upon request to and with permission from the
25 department, a municipality or local lake association or similar nonprofit organization may
26 display at state boat launch facilities a single sign, not to exceed 24 inches by 36 inches,
27 about promoting healthy lake water quality and reducing the risk of introduction of invasive
28 aquatic species.'
29 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
30 number to read consecutively.
31 SUMMARY
3322 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment provides that
3333 upon request to and with permission from the Department of Inland Fisheries and Wildlife,
3344 a municipality or local lake association or similar nonprofit organization may display at
Page 1 - 132LR0654(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 944, L.D. 1435
315 state boat launch facilities a single sign about promoting healthy lake water quality and
326 reducing the risk of introduction of invasive aquatic species. The amendment also specifies
337 that the sign may not be larger than 24 inches by 36 inches.
348 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
359 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR0654(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
